# Backend API Conventions

## Router Structure

Routers live in `packages/api/src/routers/`. Each file exports a router object:

```ts
// packages/api/src/routers/<domain>.ts
import { protectedProcedure, adminProcedure } from "..";
import { db } from "@workspace/db";
import { tableName } from "@workspace/db/schema";
import { insertSchema, selectSchema, updateSchema } from "@workspace/db/schema/validation";
import { ORPCError } from "@orpc/server";
import { eq } from "drizzle-orm";
import { z } from "zod";

export const domainRouter = {
  list: protectedProcedure
    .output(z.array(selectSchema))
    .handler(async () => { /* ... */ }),

  get: protectedProcedure
    .input(z.object({ id: z.string().uuid() }))
    .output(selectSchema)
    .handler(async ({ input }) => { /* ... */ }),

  create: adminProcedure
    .input(insertSchema)
    .output(selectSchema)
    .handler(async ({ input }) => { /* ... */ }),

  update: adminProcedure
    .input(z.object({ id: z.string().uuid() }).merge(updateSchema))
    .output(selectSchema)
    .handler(async ({ input }) => { /* ... */ }),

  delete: adminProcedure
    .input(z.object({ id: z.string().uuid() }))
    .handler(async ({ input }) => { /* ... */ }),
};
```

Register in `packages/api/src/routers/index.ts`:

```ts
export const appRouter = {
  // ...existing routers
  domain: domainRouter,
};
```

## Procedure Access Levels

| Procedure | When to use |
|-----------|-------------|
| `publicProcedure` | No auth needed (health check, public data) |
| `protectedProcedure` | Any logged-in user |
| `managerProcedure` | Manager+ role required |
| `adminProcedure` | Admin only (CRUD mutations, org-wide ops) |

## Error Handling — Always use ORPCError

```ts
import { ORPCError } from "@orpc/server";

// ❌ BAD
throw new Error("Project not found");

// ✅ GOOD
throw new ORPCError("NOT_FOUND", { message: "Project not found" });

// Common codes: UNAUTHORIZED, FORBIDDEN, NOT_FOUND, BAD_REQUEST, INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR, CONFLICT
```

## CRUD Patterns

```ts
// CREATE — generate UUID, insert, return
const id = crypto.randomUUID();
const [created] = await db.insert(table).values({ id, ...input }).returning();
if (!created) throw new ORPCError("INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR", { message: "Failed to create" });
return created;

// UPDATE — destructure id, update rest
const { id, ...data } = input;
const [updated] = await db.update(table).set(data).where(eq(table.id, id)).returning();
if (!updated) throw new ORPCError("NOT_FOUND");
return updated;

// DELETE
await db.delete(table).where(eq(table.id, input.id));
return { success: true };

// UPSERT
await db.insert(table).values(input)
  .onConflictDoUpdate({ target: table.uniqueCol, set: input });
```

## Validation (drizzle-zod)

Define in `packages/db/src/schema/validation.ts`:

```ts
import { createInsertSchema, createSelectSchema } from "drizzle-zod";

export const selectEntitySchema = createSelectSchema(entity);
export const insertEntitySchema = createInsertSchema(entity).omit({
  id: true,
  createdAt: true,
  updatedAt: true,
});
export const updateEntitySchema = insertEntitySchema.partial();
```

## Streaming Routes (Hono, not oRPC)

For AI/streaming endpoints that need SSE or chunked responses, use raw Hono routes in `apps/server/src/routes/`:

```ts
// apps/server/src/routes/<name>.ts
import { Hono } from "hono";
import { auth } from "@workspace/auth";

const routes = new Hono();

routes.post("/endpoint", async (c) => {
  const session = await auth.api.getSession({ headers: c.req.raw.headers });
  if (!session) return c.json({ error: "Unauthorized" }, 401);

  // streaming logic...
  return new Response(stream, { headers: { "Content-Type": "text/event-stream" } });
});

export { routes as featureRoutes };
```

Register in `apps/server/src/index.ts`: `app.route("/prefix", featureRoutes);`

## Database Schema

- Tables in `packages/db/src/schema/` using `pgTable`, `pgEnum`
- Relations via `relations()` for Drizzle relational queries
- Sensitive data: use `encrypt`/`decrypt` from `packages/db/src/crypto.ts` (AES-256-GCM)
- Migrations: `drizzle-kit` (`pnpm db:generate`, `pnpm db:migrate`)

## Context & Auth

Per-request context built in `packages/api/src/context.ts`:
- Reads session from Better Auth via request headers
- Available as `context.session.user` in protected+ procedures
